PN,30201
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1772016033
OL,3,CCouncils leave children as young as
OL,4,Cfour sleeping on the streets, ITV News
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FITV News has found that children as
OL,8,Fyoung as four years old are being
OL,9,Fforced to sleep rough on the streets,
OL,10,Fwith local councils in England being
OL,11,Faccused of breaking the law by denying
OL,12,Ffamilies emergency accommodation.
OL,14,FWe spoke to one homeless family in
OL,15,FLondon with five children who slept on
OL,16,Fthe streets for almost two weeks in
OL,17,FDecember, and another family with
OL,18,Fthree children in Birmingham, all
OL,19,Funder the age of 12, who were forced
OL,20,Fto sleep in their car.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1772016033
OL,3,CCouncils leave children as young as
OL,4,Cfour sleeping on the streets, ITV News
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FBoth families were turned away by
OL,8,Flocal councils, who refused to provide
OL,9,Fthe accommodation after they became
OL,10,Fhomeless.
OL,12,FThe charity Crisis says councils are
OL,13,Fincreasingly "competing with each
OL,14,Fother to not help children rough
OL,15,Fsleeping, which is something I thought
OL,16,Fwe'd never see".
OL,18,FMatt Downie, the CEO of Crisis, says
OL,19,F'we're seeing councils flagrantly
OL,20,Fbreaking their own laws'
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1772016033
OL,3,CCouncils leave children as young as
OL,4,Cfour sleeping on the streets, ITV News
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FThe charity told ITV News their
OL,8,Frecords show 100 homeless, including
OL,9,Ffamilies with children and pregnant
OL,10,Fmothers, have come to them for help
OL,11,Fafter being turned away by local
OL,12,Fauthorities.
OL,14,F"In the last few weeks and months,
OL,15,Fwe've started to see something we've
OL,16,Fnever seen before. We have never seen
OL,17,Fchildren having to sleep rough in this
OL,18,Fcountry," said Matt Downie, Crisis CEO.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1772016033
OL,3,CCouncils leave children as young as
OL,4,Cfour sleeping on the streets, ITV News
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,F"We very often are understanding of
OL,8,Fthe pressures that local councils are
OL,9,Funder because they are real, but when
OL,10,Fit comes to children sleeping rough,
OL,11,FI'm afraid there's no sympathy
OL,12,Fwhatsoever.
OL,14,F"You're breaking the law. It's morally
OL,15,Foutrageous. It's legally outrageous.
OL,16,FIt needs to stop and we need the
OL,17,Fgovernment to step in and say
OL,18,Funequivocally, this must never happen
OL,19,Fagain."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1772016033
OL,3,CCouncils leave children as young as
OL,4,Cfour sleeping on the streets, ITV News
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FAccording to the government, a
OL,8,Fhousehold with a child has a priority
OL,9,Fneed and should be provided with
OL,10,Ftemporary accommodation if homeless.
OL,12,FIf you or your family have been
OL,13,Faffected by this story you can contact
OL,14,Fus at investigations@itv.com
OL,16,FIf the household does not meet the
OL,17,Fcriteria for homelessness assistance,
OL,18,Fthen children's services should
OL,19,Faccommodate them to protect the
OL,20,Fwelfare of the children.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1772016033
OL,3,CCouncils leave children as young as
OL,4,Cfour sleeping on the streets, ITV News
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FIn cases where it is not clear which
OL,8,Fauthority owes a duty to accommodate,
OL,9,Fthe local authority approached by the
OL,10,Ffamily should provide interim
OL,11,Faccommodation while inquiries are made
OL,12,For disputes resolved.
OL,14,FIn south London, five children and
OL,15,Ftheir parents became street homeless
OL,16,Fin December after being refused to
OL,17,Fprovide them with accommodation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1772016033
OL,3,CCouncils leave children as young as
OL,4,Cfour sleeping on the streets, ITV News
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FThe family, who are from Afghanistan,
OL,8,Fare refugees with the legal right to
OL,9,Flive in the UK. They fled the Taliban,
OL,10,Fso we are protecting their identity.
OL,12,FThey became homeless in November 2025.
OL,13,FUnable to find anywhere affordable to
OL,14,Frent, they approached the council in
OL,15,FBromley, where their father had been
OL,16,Fliving since 2022.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1772016033
OL,3,CCouncils leave children as young as
OL,4,Cfour sleeping on the streets, ITV News
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FDespite turning up at the council
OL,8,Fbuilding, the children aged 4, 8, 12,
OL,9,F16 and 18, and their parents were told
OL,10,Fthe council had no duty to provide
OL,11,Faccommodation.
OL,13,FWith nowhere else to go, they slept on
OL,14,Fthe streets for 12 nights.
OL,16,F"The weather was very cold, and it was
OL,17,Fraining," said the children's father.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1772016033
OL,3,CCouncils leave children as young as
OL,4,Cfour sleeping on the streets, ITV News
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,F"People were crossing from the road,
OL,8,Fgiving us blankets, and they helped
OL,9,Fus. I was thinking - my children could
OL,10,Fdie, anything could happen.
OL,12,F"The children told me when we lived in
OL,13,FAfghanistan, we were helping beggars,
OL,14,Fwe used to take food to them - how
OL,15,Fcome we are in this situation here?
OL,17,F"The way they are treating us is worse
OL,18,Fthan animals - they are children."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1772016033
OL,3,CCouncils leave children as young as
OL,4,Cfour sleeping on the streets, ITV News
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FThe family travelled to Walthamstow in
OL,8,Fnorth-east London, where they hoped to
OL,9,Fstay with people they knew. When they
OL,10,Fwere unable to stay there, they
OL,11,Fapproached Waltham Forest Council.
OL,13,FThey slept on the steps of the council
OL,14,Fbuilding, before being found by
OL,15,Fcharity workers from Crisis and placed
OL,16,Fin a local hostel. Waltham Forest then
OL,17,Fagreed to pay for emergency
OL,18,Faccommodation after 12 nights on the
OL,19,Fstreets.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1772016033
OL,3,CCouncils leave children as young as
OL,4,Cfour sleeping on the streets, ITV News
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,F"Secretly, I cried. I cried when I was
OL,8,Fon the streets," said the father.
OL,10,F"I was thinking here there would human
OL,11,Frights - if they don't care about me,
OL,12,Fthey should care about my children."
OL,14,FThe family is currently living in a
OL,15,Fhostel.
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/21
